Package com.meetwise.fs

Contains the file-system independent classes and interfaces, as well as the FileSystemFactory for creating FileSystem instances.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BlockDevice This is the abstraction used for a device that can hold a FileSystem.
FileSystem The interface common to all file system implementations.
FSDirectory Base class for all FileSystem directories.
FSDirectoryEntry Represents one entry in a FSDirectory.
FSFile A FSFile is a representation of a single block of bytes on a filesystem.
FSObject This interface is the base interface for objects that are part of a FileSystem.
 

Class Summary
AbstractFileSystem Abstract class with common things in different FileSystem implementations.
BootSector The boot sector.
FileSystemFactory Factory for FileSystem instances.
Sector  
 

Exception Summary
FileSystemException Base class for all exceptions that can be generated by a FileSystem.
FileSystemFullException Gets thrown when a file system can not store the additional data that is tried to be written.
ReadOnlyDeviceException This exception is thrown by a BlockDevice if there is an attempt to write to a read-only device.
ReadOnlyFileSystemException Exception allowing to handle cases where a FileSystem is mounted readOnly.
UnknownFileSystemException Indicates that it was not possible to determine the file system being used on a block device.
 

Package com.meetwise.fs Description

Contains the file-system independent classes and interfaces, as well as the FileSystemFactory for creating FileSystem instances.
